Limamin Cocin Anglican da ya lashe lambar yabo ta Victoria Cross a matsayin mai yaƙi a yakin duniya na farko an yi bikin a garinsa bayan shekaru 100.
Lt. Col. Bernard Vann ya sami lambar yabo a ranar 29 ga Satumba, 1918 a harin Bellenglise da Lehaucourt.
Wani dan bindiga ya kashe shi bayan kwana hudu, kuma bai san cewa an ba shi babbar girmamawa ta soja a Burtaniya ba.
An kaddamar da wani dutse na tunawa da shi a ranar Asabar da jikokinsa biyu suka kaddamar a lokacin bikin a Rushden, Northamptonshire.
Ɗaya daga cikin jikokin, Michael Vann, ya ce yana da "ban mamaki da alama" cewa za a bayyana dutsen daidai shekaru 100 bayan da kakansa ya lashe lambar yabo.
A cewar London Gazette, a ranar 29 ga Satumba, 1918, Lieutenant Colonel Vann ya jagoranci dakarunsa a kan Canal de Saint-Quentin  cikin hazo mai yawa da kuma wuta mai ƙarfi na bindigogi da na'urori.
Daga baya, ya hanzarta zuwa layin farko kuma, tare da "ƙwarewar ƙarfin hali", ya buɗe hanyar sojoji, sannan ya kai hari ga gidan bindiga shi kaɗai kuma ya sami nasarar kawar da makamai uku na tawagar.
An kashe Lieutenant Colonel Vann ta hanyar wani dan Jamus mai harbi a ranar 4 ga Oktoba, 1918, kawai wata daya kafin karshen yakin.
Michael Vann, mai shekara 72, ya ce abin da kakansa ya yi "wani abu ne da na sani ba zan taɓa iya daidaitawa ba, amma abin da ya sa ni tawali'u".
Shi da ɗan'uwansa, Dr. James Vann, sun kuma saka kambi bayan bikin, wanda Orchestra na Matasa na Brentwood Imperial ya gudanar.
Michael Vann ya ce yana jin daɗin taka rawa a cikin wannan bikin kuma ya kara da cewa, "yawan jarumin na gaskiya ya nuna goyon bayan da mutane da yawa ke ba shi".
